Deutsche Telekom, Portugal Telecom: European Equity Preview

-- B y   I n y o u n g   H w a n g
-- 
2011-09-16T04:00:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-15/deutsche-telekom-portugal-telecom-european-equity-preview.html
The following companies’ shares may
be active in European trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses.  The Stoxx Europe 600 Index increased 2 percent to 228.69.
The Stoxx 50 Index rose 2 percent to 2,149.12. The Euro Stoxx 50
Index, a benchmark for nations using the euro, climbed 3.5
percent to 2,155.62.  Bayer AG (BAYN)  : The drugmaker plans to restructure its
diagnostics business and may seek a buyer for part of the unit,
Financial Times Deutschland reported. The shares rose 0.6
percent to 38.96 euros.  Deutsche Telekom (DTE GY):  AT&T Inc. (T)  and the U.S. Justice
Department agreed on a plan for handling confidential data in
the government’s antitrust lawsuit seeking to block the
company’s purchase of wireless carrier T-Mobile USA Inc., a unit
of Deutsche Telekom. Deutsche Telekom shares rose 1.3 percent to
8.48 euros.  Endesa SA (ELE)  ,  Gas Natural SDG SA (GAS)  ,  Iberdrola
SA (IBE)  : Spanish electricity companies may be active after
the nation’s power regulator said it doesn’t see a case for
paying them for back-up generating capacity and the nuclear
regulator said it will recommend improvements to safety
measures.  Endesa shares climbed 2.4 percent to 17.18 euros. Gas
Natural shares rose 4.3 percent to 12.26 euros. Iberdrola shares
gained 5.4 percent to 5.03 euros.  Portugal Telecom SGPS SA (PTC)  :  Portugal ’s biggest
telecommunications company said Banco Espirito Santo SA holds an
11.25 percent stake. The shares gained 0.2 percent to 5.61
euros.  To contact the reporter on this story:
